         <abstract>
            <p>The Minkowski method of unit search is applied to particular types of parallelotopes permitting to discover algebraic integers of bounded norm in a given algebraic number field of degree $n$ at will by solving successively $2n$ linear inequalities for one unknown each. Application is made to the unit search for all totally real number fields of minimal discriminant for $n \leqslant 7$.</p>
